69// The ratio between kVTCompressionPropertyKey_DataRateLimits and
70// kVTCompressionPropertyKey_AverageBitRate. The data rate limit is set higher
71// than the average bit rate to avoid undershooting the target.
72const float kLimitToAverageBitRateFactor = 1.5f;
73// These thresholds deviate from the default h264 QP thresholds, as they
74// have been found to work better on devices that support VideoToolbox
75const int kLowH264QpThreshold = 28;
76const int kHighH264QpThreshold = 39;
77
78const OSType kNV12PixelFormat = kCVPixelFormatType_420YpCbCr8BiPlanarFullRange;
79
80const int kBelowFrameRateThreshold = 2;
81const int kBelowFrameRateBitRateDecrease = 3;
82
83// Struct that we pass to the encoder per frame to encode. We receive it again
84// in the encoder callback.
85struct RTCFrameEncodeParams {
86 RTCFrameEncodeParams(RTCVideoEncoderH264 *e,
87 RTCCodecSpecificInfoH264 *csi,
88 int32_t w,
89 int32_t h,
90 int64_t rtms,
91 uint32_t ts,
92 RTCVideoRotation r,
93 bool isKeyFrameRequired)
94 : encoder(e), width(w), height(h), render_time_ms(rtms), timestamp(ts), rotation(r), isKeyFrameRequired(isKeyFrameRequired) {
95 if (csi) {
96 codecSpecificInfo = csi;
97 } else {
98 codecSpecificInfo = [[RTCCodecSpecificInfoH264 alloc] init];
99 }
100 }
101
102 RTCVideoEncoderH264 *encoder;
103 RTCCodecSpecificInfoH264 *codecSpecificInfo;
104 int32_t width;
105 int32_t height;
106 int64_t render_time_ms;
107 uint32_t timestamp;
108 RTCVideoRotation rotation;
109 bool isKeyFrameRequired;
110};

112// We receive I420Frames as input, but we need to feed CVPixelBuffers into the
113// encoder. This performs the copy and format conversion.
114// TODO(tkchin): See if encoder will accept i420 frames and compare performance.
115bool CopyVideoFrameToNV12PixelBuffer(id<RTCI420Buffer> frameBuffer, CVPixelBufferRef pixelBuffer) {
116 RTC_DCHECK(pixelBuffer);
117 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(CVPixelBufferGetPixelFormatType(pixelBuffer), kNV12PixelFormat);
118 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(CVPixelBufferGetHeightOfPlane(pixelBuffer, 0), frameBuffer.height);
119 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(CVPixelBufferGetWidthOfPlane(pixelBuffer, 0), frameBuffer.width);
120
121 CVReturn cvRet = CVPixelBufferLockBaseAddress(pixelBuffer, 0);
122 if (cvRet != kCVReturnSuccess) {
123 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to lock base address: " << cvRet;
124 return false;
125 }
126 uint8_t *dstY = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t *>(CVPixelBufferGetBaseAddressOfPlane(pixelBuffer, 0));
127 int dstStrideY = CVPixelBufferGetBytesPerRowOfPlane(pixelBuffer, 0);
128 uint8_t *dstUV = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t *>(CVPixelBufferGetBaseAddressOfPlane(pixelBuffer, 1));
129 int dstStrideUV = CVPixelBufferGetBytesPerRowOfPlane(pixelBuffer, 1);
130 // Convert I420 to NV12.
131 int ret = libyuv::I420ToNV12(frameBuffer.dataY,
132 frameBuffer.strideY,
133 frameBuffer.dataU,
134 frameBuffer.strideU,
135 frameBuffer.dataV,
136 frameBuffer.strideV,
137 dstY,
138 dstStrideY,
139 dstUV,
140 dstStrideUV,
141 frameBuffer.width,
142 frameBuffer.height);
143 CVPixelBufferUnlockBaseAddress(pixelBuffer, 0);
144 if (ret) {
145 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Error converting I420 VideoFrame to NV12 :" << ret;
146 return false;
147 }
148 return true;
149}
150
151CVPixelBufferRef CreatePixelBuffer(CVPixelBufferPoolRef pixel_buffer_pool) {
152 if (!pixel_buffer_pool) {
153 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to get pixel buffer pool.";
154 return nullptr;
155 }
156 CVPixelBufferRef pixel_buffer;
157 CVReturn ret = CVPixelBufferPoolCreatePixelBuffer(nullptr, pixel_buffer_pool, &pixel_buffer);
158 if (ret != kCVReturnSuccess) {
159 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to create pixel buffer: " << ret;
160 // We probably want to drop frames here, since failure probably means
161 // that the pool is empty.
162 return nullptr;
163 }
164 return pixel_buffer;
165}

167// This is the callback function that VideoToolbox calls when encode is
168// complete. From inspection this happens on its own queue.
169void compressionOutputCallback(void *encoder,
170 void *params,
171 OSStatus status,
172 VTEncodeInfoFlags infoFlags,
173 CMSampleBufferRef sampleBuffer) {
174 if (!params) {
175 // If there are pending callbacks when the encoder is destroyed, this can happen.
176 return;
177 }
178 std::unique_ptr<RTCFrameEncodeParams> encodeParams(
179 reinterpret_cast<RTCFrameEncodeParams *>(params));
180 [encodeParams->encoder frameWasEncoded:status
181 flags:infoFlags
182 sampleBuffer:sampleBuffer
183 codecSpecificInfo:encodeParams->codecSpecificInfo
184 width:encodeParams->width
185 height:encodeParams->height
186 renderTimeMs:encodeParams->render_time_ms
187 timestamp:encodeParams->timestamp
188 rotation:encodeParams->rotation
189 isKeyFrameRequired:encodeParams->isKeyFrameRequired];
190}
191
192// Extract VideoToolbox profile out of the webrtc::SdpVideoFormat. If there is
193// no specific VideoToolbox profile for the specified level, AutoLevel will be
194// returned. The user must initialize the encoder with a resolution and
195// framerate conforming to the selected H264 level regardless.
196CFStringRef ExtractProfile(const webrtc::H264::ProfileLevelId &profile_level_id) {
197 switch (profile_level_id.profile) {
198 case webrtc::H264::kProfileConstrainedBaseline:
199 case webrtc::H264::kProfileBaseline:
200 switch (profile_level_id.level) {
201 case webrtc::H264::kLevel3:
202 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_Baseline_3_0;
203 case webrtc::H264::kLevel3_1:
204 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_Baseline_3_1;
205 case webrtc::H264::kLevel3_2:
206 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_Baseline_3_2;
207 case webrtc::H264::kLevel4:
208 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_Baseline_4_0;
209 case webrtc::H264::kLevel4_1:
210 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_Baseline_4_1;
211 case webrtc::H264::kLevel4_2:
212 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_Baseline_4_2;
213 case webrtc::H264::kLevel5:
214 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_Baseline_5_0;
215 case webrtc::H264::kLevel5_1:
216 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_Baseline_5_1;
217 case webrtc::H264::kLevel5_2:
218 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_Baseline_5_2;
219 case webrtc::H264::kLevel1:
220 case webrtc::H264::kLevel1_b:
221 case webrtc::H264::kLevel1_1:
222 case webrtc::H264::kLevel1_2:
223 case webrtc::H264::kLevel1_3:
224 case webrtc::H264::kLevel2:
225 case webrtc::H264::kLevel2_1:
226 case webrtc::H264::kLevel2_2:
227 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_Baseline_AutoLevel;
228 }
229
230 case webrtc::H264::kProfileMain:
231 switch (profile_level_id.level) {
232 case webrtc::H264::kLevel3:
233 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_Main_3_0;
234 case webrtc::H264::kLevel3_1:
235 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_Main_3_1;
236 case webrtc::H264::kLevel3_2:
237 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_Main_3_2;
238 case webrtc::H264::kLevel4:
239 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_Main_4_0;
240 case webrtc::H264::kLevel4_1:
241 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_Main_4_1;
242 case webrtc::H264::kLevel4_2:
243 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_Main_4_2;
244 case webrtc::H264::kLevel5:
245 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_Main_5_0;
246 case webrtc::H264::kLevel5_1:
247 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_Main_5_1;
248 case webrtc::H264::kLevel5_2:
249 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_Main_5_2;
250 case webrtc::H264::kLevel1:
251 case webrtc::H264::kLevel1_b:
252 case webrtc::H264::kLevel1_1:
253 case webrtc::H264::kLevel1_2:
254 case webrtc::H264::kLevel1_3:
255 case webrtc::H264::kLevel2:
256 case webrtc::H264::kLevel2_1:
257 case webrtc::H264::kLevel2_2:
258 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_Main_AutoLevel;
259 }
260
261 case webrtc::H264::kProfileConstrainedHigh:
262 case webrtc::H264::kProfileHigh:
263 switch (profile_level_id.level) {
264 case webrtc::H264::kLevel3:
265 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_High_3_0;
266 case webrtc::H264::kLevel3_1:
267 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_High_3_1;
268 case webrtc::H264::kLevel3_2:
269 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_High_3_2;
270 case webrtc::H264::kLevel4:
271 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_High_4_0;
272 case webrtc::H264::kLevel4_1:
273 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_High_4_1;
274 case webrtc::H264::kLevel4_2:
275 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_High_4_2;
276 case webrtc::H264::kLevel5:
277 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_High_5_0;
278 case webrtc::H264::kLevel5_1:
279 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_High_5_1;
280 case webrtc::H264::kLevel5_2:
281 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_High_5_2;
282 case webrtc::H264::kLevel1:
283 case webrtc::H264::kLevel1_b:
284 case webrtc::H264::kLevel1_1:
285 case webrtc::H264::kLevel1_2:
286 case webrtc::H264::kLevel1_3:
287 case webrtc::H264::kLevel2:
288 case webrtc::H264::kLevel2_1:
289 case webrtc::H264::kLevel2_2:
290 return kVTProfileLevel_H264_High_AutoLevel;
291 }
292 }
293}

295// The function returns the max allowed sample rate (pixels per second) that
296// can be processed by given encoder with |profile_level_id|.
297// See https://www.itu.int/rec/dologin_pub.asp?lang=e&id=T-REC-H.264-201610-S!!PDF-E&type=items
298// for details.
299NSUInteger GetMaxSampleRate(const webrtc::H264::ProfileLevelId &profile_level_id) {
300 switch (profile_level_id.level) {
301 case webrtc::H264::kLevel3:
302 return 10368000;
303 case webrtc::H264::kLevel3_1:
304 return 27648000;
305 case webrtc::H264::kLevel3_2:
306 return 55296000;
307 case webrtc::H264::kLevel4:
308 case webrtc::H264::kLevel4_1:
309 return 62914560;
310 case webrtc::H264::kLevel4_2:
311 return 133693440;
312 case webrtc::H264::kLevel5:
313 return 150994944;
314 case webrtc::H264::kLevel5_1:
315 return 251658240;
316 case webrtc::H264::kLevel5_2:
317 return 530841600;
318 case webrtc::H264::kLevel1:
319 case webrtc::H264::kLevel1_b:
320 case webrtc::H264::kLevel1_1:
321 case webrtc::H264::kLevel1_2:
322 case webrtc::H264::kLevel1_3:
323 case webrtc::H264::kLevel2:
324 case webrtc::H264::kLevel2_1:
325 case webrtc::H264::kLevel2_2:
326 // Zero means auto rate setting.
327 return 0;
328 }
329}

332@implementation RTCVideoEncoderH264 {
333 RTCVideoCodecInfo *_codecInfo;
334 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::BitrateAdjuster> _bitrateAdjuster;
335 uint32_t _targetBitrateBps;
336 uint32_t _encoderBitrateBps;
337 uint32_t _encoderFrameRate;
338 uint32_t _maxAllowedFrameRate;
339 RTCH264PacketizationMode _packetizationMode;
340 absl::optional<webrtc::H264::ProfileLevelId> _profile_level_id;
341 RTCVideoEncoderCallback _callback;
342 int32_t _width;
343 int32_t _height;
344 bool _useVCP;
345 bool _useBaseline;
346 VTCompressionSessionRef _vtCompressionSession;
347 VCPCompressionSessionRef _vcpCompressionSession;
348 CVPixelBufferPoolRef _pixelBufferPool;
349 RTCVideoCodecMode _mode;
350
351 webrtc::H264BitstreamParser _h264BitstreamParser;
352 std::vector<uint8_t> _frameScaleBuffer;
353 bool _disableEncoding;
354 bool _isKeyFrameRequired;
355 bool _isH264LowLatencyEncoderEnabled;
356 bool _isUsingSoftwareEncoder;
357 bool _isBelowExpectedFrameRate;
358 uint32_t _frameCount;
359 int64_t _lastFrameRateEstimationTime;
360}
361
362// .5 is set as a mininum to prevent overcompensating for large temporary
363// overshoots. We don't want to degrade video quality too badly.
364// .95 is set to prevent oscillations. When a lower bitrate is set on the
365// encoder than previously set, its output seems to have a brief period of
366// drastically reduced bitrate, so we want to avoid that. In steady state
367// conditions, 0.95 seems to give us better overall bitrate over long periods
368// of time.
369- (instancetype)initWithCodecInfo:(RTCVideoCodecInfo *)codecInfo {
370 if (self = [super init]) {
371 _codecInfo = codecInfo;
372 _bitrateAdjuster.reset(new webrtc::BitrateAdjuster(.5, .95));
373 _packetizationMode = RTCH264PacketizationModeNonInterleaved;
374 _profile_level_id =
375 webrtc::H264::ParseSdpProfileLevelId([codecInfo nativeSdpVideoFormat].parameters);
376 _useBaseline = !_profile_level_id || ![(__bridge NSString *)ExtractProfile(*_profile_level_id) containsString: @"High"];
377#if ENABLE_VCP_FOR_H264_BASELINE
378 _useVCP = true;
379#else
380 _useVCP = !_useBaseline;
381#endif
382 RTC_DCHECK(_profile_level_id);
383 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Using profile " << CFStringToString(ExtractProfile(*_profile_level_id));
384 RTC_CHECK([codecInfo.name isEqualToString:kRTCVideoCodecH264Name]);
385 }
386 _isKeyFrameRequired = false;
387 _isH264LowLatencyEncoderEnabled = true;
388 _isUsingSoftwareEncoder = false;
389 _isBelowExpectedFrameRate = false;
390 _frameCount = 0;
391 _lastFrameRateEstimationTime = 0;
392 return self;
393}

396{
397 _isH264LowLatencyEncoderEnabled = enabled;
398}

400- (void)dealloc {
401 [self destroyCompressionSession];

404- (NSInteger)startEncodeWithSettings:(RTCVideoEncoderSettings *)settings
405 numberOfCores:(int)numberOfCores {
406 RTC_DCHECK(settings);
407 RTC_DCHECK([settings.name isEqualToString:kRTCVideoCodecH264Name]);
408
409 _width = settings.width;
410 _height = settings.height;
411 _mode = settings.mode;
412
413 uint32_t aligned_width = (((_width + 15) >> 4) << 4);
414 uint32_t aligned_height = (((_height + 15) >> 4) << 4);
415 _maxAllowedFrameRate = static_cast<uint32_t>(GetMaxSampleRate(*_profile_level_id) /
416 (aligned_width * aligned_height));
417
418 // We can only set average bitrate on the HW encoder.
419 _targetBitrateBps = settings.startBitrate * 1000; // startBitrate is in kbps.
420 _bitrateAdjuster->SetTargetBitrateBps(_targetBitrateBps);
421 _encoderFrameRate = MIN(settings.maxFramerate, _maxAllowedFrameRate);
422 if (settings.maxFramerate > _maxAllowedFrameRate && _maxAllowedFrameRate > 0) {
423 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Initial encoder frame rate setting " << settings.maxFramerate
424 << " is larger than the "
425 << "maximal allowed frame rate " << _maxAllowedFrameRate << ".";
426 }
427
428 // TODO(tkchin): Try setting payload size via
429 // kVTCompressionPropertyKey_MaxH264SliceBytes.
430
431 return [self resetCompressionSessionWithPixelFormat:kNV12PixelFormat];
432}
433
434- (bool)hasCompressionSession
435{
436 return _vtCompressionSession || _vcpCompressionSession;
437}
438
439- (NSInteger)encode:(RTCVideoFrame *)frame
440 codecSpecificInfo:(nullable id<RTCCodecSpecificInfo>)codecSpecificInfo
441 frameTypes:(NSArray<NSNumber *> *)frameTypes {
442 if (!_callback || ![self hasCompressionSession]) {
443 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_UNINITIALIZED;
444 }
445 BOOL isKeyframeRequired = _isKeyFrameRequired;
446 _isKeyFrameRequired = false;
447
448 // Get a pixel buffer from the pool and copy frame data over.
449 if ([self resetCompressionSessionIfNeededWithFrame:frame]) {
450 isKeyframeRequired = YES;
451 }
452
453 if (_disableEncoding) {
454 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
455 }
456 if (_isUsingSoftwareEncoder) {
457 [self updateBitRateAccordingActualFrameRate];
458 }
459
460 CVPixelBufferRef pixelBuffer = nullptr;
461 if ([frame.buffer isKindOfClass:[RTCCVPixelBuffer class]]) {
462 // Native frame buffer
463 RTCCVPixelBuffer *rtcPixelBuffer = (RTCCVPixelBuffer *)frame.buffer;
464 if (![rtcPixelBuffer requiresCropping]) {
465 // This pixel buffer might have a higher resolution than what the
466 // compression session is configured to. The compression session can
467 // handle that and will output encoded frames in the configured
468 // resolution regardless of the input pixel buffer resolution.
469 pixelBuffer = rtcPixelBuffer.pixelBuffer;
470 CVBufferRetain(pixelBuffer);
471 } else {
472 // Cropping required, we need to crop and scale to a new pixel buffer.
473 pixelBuffer = CreatePixelBuffer(_pixelBufferPool);
474 if (!pixelBuffer) {
475 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
476 }
477 int dstWidth = CVPixelBufferGetWidth(pixelBuffer);
478 int dstHeight = CVPixelBufferGetHeight(pixelBuffer);
479 if ([rtcPixelBuffer requiresScalingToWidth:dstWidth height:dstHeight]) {
480 int size =
481 [rtcPixelBuffer bufferSizeForCroppingAndScalingToWidth:dstWidth height:dstHeight];
482 _frameScaleBuffer.resize(size);
483 } else {
484 _frameScaleBuffer.clear();
485 }
486 _frameScaleBuffer.shrink_to_fit();
487 if (![rtcPixelBuffer cropAndScaleTo:pixelBuffer withTempBuffer:_frameScaleBuffer.data()]) {
488 CVBufferRelease(pixelBuffer);
489 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
490 }
491 }
492 }
493
494 if (!pixelBuffer) {
495 // We did not have a native frame buffer
496 pixelBuffer = CreatePixelBuffer(_pixelBufferPool);
497 if (!pixelBuffer) {
498 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
499 }
500 RTC_DCHECK(pixelBuffer);
501 if (!CopyVideoFrameToNV12PixelBuffer([frame.buffer toI420], pixelBuffer)) {
502 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to copy frame data.";
503 CVBufferRelease(pixelBuffer);
504 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
505 }
506 }
507
508 // Check if we need a keyframe.
509 if (!isKeyframeRequired && frameTypes) {
510 for (NSNumber *frameType in frameTypes) {
511 if ((RTCFrameType)frameType.intValue == RTCFrameTypeVideoFrameKey) {
512 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "keyframe requested";
513 isKeyframeRequired = YES;
514 break;
515 }
516 }
517 }
518
519 CMTime presentationTimeStamp = CMTimeMake(frame.timeStampNs / rtc::kNumNanosecsPerMillisec, 1000);
520 CFDictionaryRef frameProperties = nullptr;
521 if (isKeyframeRequired) {
522 CFTypeRef keys[] = {kVTEncodeFrameOptionKey_ForceKeyFrame};
523 CFTypeRef values[] = {kCFBooleanTrue};
524 frameProperties = CreateCFTypeDictionary(keys, values, 1);
525 }
526
527 std::unique_ptr<RTCFrameEncodeParams> encodeParams;
528 encodeParams.reset(new RTCFrameEncodeParams(self,
529 codecSpecificInfo,
530 _width,
531 _height,
532 frame.timeStampNs / rtc::kNumNanosecsPerMillisec,
533 frame.timeStamp,
534 frame.rotation,
535 isKeyframeRequired));
536 encodeParams->codecSpecificInfo.packetizationMode = _packetizationMode;
537
538 // Update the bitrate if needed.
539 [self setBitrateBps:_bitrateAdjuster->GetAdjustedBitrateBps() frameRate:_encoderFrameRate];
540
541 OSStatus status;
542 if (_vtCompressionSession) {
543 status = VTCompressionSessionEncodeFrame(_vtCompressionSession,
544 pixelBuffer,
545 presentationTimeStamp,
546 kCMTimeInvalid,
547 frameProperties,
548 encodeParams.release(),
549 nullptr);
550 } else {
551#if ENABLE_VCP_ENCODER
552 status = webrtc::VCPCompressionSessionEncodeFrame(_vcpCompressionSession,
553 pixelBuffer,
554 presentationTimeStamp,
555 kCMTimeInvalid,
556 frameProperties,
557 encodeParams.release(),
558 nullptr);
559#else
560 status = 1;
561#endif
562 }
563 if (frameProperties) {
564 CFRelease(frameProperties);
565 }
566 if (pixelBuffer) {
567 CVBufferRelease(pixelBuffer);
568 }
569
570 if (status == kVTInvalidSessionErr) {
571 // This error occurs when entering foreground after backgrounding the app.
572 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Invalid compression session, resetting.";
573 [self resetCompressionSessionWithPixelFormat:[self pixelFormatOfFrame:frame]];
574
575 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_NO_OUTPUT;
576 } else if (status == kVTVideoEncoderMalfunctionErr) {
577 // Sometimes the encoder malfunctions and needs to be restarted.
578 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
579 << "Encountered video encoder malfunction error. Resetting compression session.";
580 [self resetCompressionSessionWithPixelFormat:[self pixelFormatOfFrame:frame]];
581
582 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_NO_OUTPUT;
583 } else if (status != noErr) {
584 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to encode frame with code: " << status;
585 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
586 }
587 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
588}
589
590- (void)setCallback:(RTCVideoEncoderCallback)callback {
591 _callback = callback;
592}
593
594- (int)setBitrate:(uint32_t)bitrateKbit framerate:(uint32_t)framerate {
595 _targetBitrateBps = 1000 * bitrateKbit;
596 _bitrateAdjuster->SetTargetBitrateBps(_targetBitrateBps);
597 if (framerate > _maxAllowedFrameRate && _maxAllowedFrameRate > 0) {
598 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Encoder frame rate setting " << framerate << " is larger than the "
599 << "maximal allowed frame rate " << _maxAllowedFrameRate << ".";
600 }
601 framerate = MIN(framerate, _maxAllowedFrameRate);
602 [self setBitrateBps:_bitrateAdjuster->GetAdjustedBitrateBps() frameRate:framerate];
603 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
604}
605
606#pragma mark - Private
607
608- (NSInteger)releaseEncoder {
609 // Need to destroy so that the session is invalidated and won't use the
610 // callback anymore. Do not remove callback until the session is invalidated
611 // since async encoder callbacks can occur until invalidation.
612 [self destroyCompressionSession];
613 _callback = nullptr;
614 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
615}

617- (OSType)pixelFormatOfFrame:(RTCVideoFrame *)frame {
618 // Use NV12 for non-native frames.
619 if ([frame.buffer isKindOfClass:[RTCCVPixelBuffer class]]) {
620 RTCCVPixelBuffer *rtcPixelBuffer = (RTCCVPixelBuffer *)frame.buffer;
621 return CVPixelBufferGetPixelFormatType(rtcPixelBuffer.pixelBuffer);
622 }
623
624 return kNV12PixelFormat;
625}
626
627- (BOOL)resetCompressionSessionIfNeededWithFrame:(RTCVideoFrame *)frame {
628 BOOL resetCompressionSession = NO;
629
630 // If we're capturing native frames in another pixel format than the compression session is
631 // configured with, make sure the compression session is reset using the correct pixel format.
632 OSType framePixelFormat = [self pixelFormatOfFrame:frame];
633
634 if ([self hasCompressionSession]) {
635#if defined(WEBRTC_WEBKIT_BUILD)
636 if (!_pixelBufferPool) {
637 return NO;
638 }
639#endif
640 // The pool attribute `kCVPixelBufferPixelFormatTypeKey` can contain either an array of pixel
641 // formats or a single pixel format.
642 NSDictionary *poolAttributes =
643 (__bridge NSDictionary *)CVPixelBufferPoolGetPixelBufferAttributes(_pixelBufferPool);
644 id pixelFormats =
645 [poolAttributes objectForKey:(__bridge NSString *)kCVPixelBufferPixelFormatTypeKey];
646 NSArray<NSNumber *> *compressionSessionPixelFormats = nil;
647 if ([pixelFormats isKindOfClass:[NSArray class]]) {
648 compressionSessionPixelFormats = (NSArray *)pixelFormats;
649 } else if ([pixelFormats isKindOfClass:[NSNumber class]]) {
650 compressionSessionPixelFormats = @[ (NSNumber *)pixelFormats ];
651 }
652
653 if (![compressionSessionPixelFormats
654 containsObject:[NSNumber numberWithLong:framePixelFormat]]) {
655 resetCompressionSession = YES;
656 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Resetting compression session due to non-matching pixel format.";
657 }
658 } else {
659 resetCompressionSession = YES;
660 }
661
662 if (resetCompressionSession) {
663 [self resetCompressionSessionWithPixelFormat:framePixelFormat];
664 }
665 return resetCompressionSession;
666}
667
668- (int)resetCompressionSessionWithPixelFormat:(OSType)framePixelFormat {
669 [self destroyCompressionSession];
670 _disableEncoding = false;
671
672 // Set source image buffer attributes. These attributes will be present on
673 // buffers retrieved from the encoder's pixel buffer pool.
674 const size_t attributesSize = 3;
675 CFTypeRef keys[attributesSize] = {
676#if defined(WEBRTC_MAC) || defined(WEBRTC_MAC_CATALYST)
677 kCVPixelBufferOpenGLCompatibilityKey,
678#elif defined(WEBRTC_IOS)
679 kCVPixelBufferOpenGLESCompatibilityKey,
680#endif
681 kCVPixelBufferIOSurfacePropertiesKey,
682 kCVPixelBufferPixelFormatTypeKey
683 };
684 CFDictionaryRef ioSurfaceValue = CreateCFTypeDictionary(nullptr, nullptr, 0);
685 int64_t pixelFormatType = framePixelFormat;
686 CFNumberRef pixelFormat = CFNumberCreate(nullptr, kCFNumberLongType, &pixelFormatType);
687 CFTypeRef values[attributesSize] = {kCFBooleanTrue, ioSurfaceValue, pixelFormat};
688 CFDictionaryRef sourceAttributes = CreateCFTypeDictionary(keys, values, attributesSize);
689 if (ioSurfaceValue) {
690 CFRelease(ioSurfaceValue);
691 ioSurfaceValue = nullptr;
692 }
693 if (pixelFormat) {
694 CFRelease(pixelFormat);
695 pixelFormat = nullptr;
696 }
697 CFMutableDictionaryRef encoderSpecs = CFDictionaryCreateMutable(nullptr, 5, &kCFTypeDictionaryKeyCallBacks, &kCFTypeDictionaryValueCallBacks);
698#if !defined(WEBRTC_IOS)
699 auto useHardwareEncoder = webrtc::isH264HardwareEncoderAllowed() ? kCFBooleanTrue : kCFBooleanFalse;
700 // Currently hw accl is supported above 360p on mac, below 360p
701 // the compression session will be created with hw accl disabled.
702 CFDictionarySetValue(encoderSpecs, kVTVideoEncoderSpecification_EnableHardwareAcceleratedVideoEncoder, useHardwareEncoder);
703#if !HAVE_VTB_REQUIREDLOWLATENCY
704 CFDictionarySetValue(encoderSpecs, kVTVideoEncoderSpecification_RequireHardwareAcceleratedVideoEncoder, useHardwareEncoder);
705#endif
706#endif
707 CFDictionarySetValue(encoderSpecs, kVTCompressionPropertyKey_RealTime, kCFBooleanTrue);
708
709#if ENABLE_VCP_ENCODER
710 if (_useVCP) {
711 int usageValue = 1;
712 auto usage = CFNumberCreate(nullptr, kCFNumberIntType, &usageValue);
713 CFDictionarySetValue(encoderSpecs, kVTCompressionPropertyKey_Usage, usage);
714 CFRelease(usage);
715#if ENABLE_VCP_VTB_ENCODER
716 CFDictionarySetValue(encoderSpecs, kVTVideoEncoderList_EncoderID, CFSTR("com.apple.videotoolbox.videoencoder.h264.rtvc"));
717#endif
718 }
719#elif HAVE_VTB_REQUIREDLOWLATENCY
720 if (_isH264LowLatencyEncoderEnabled && _useVCP)
721 CFDictionarySetValue(encoderSpecs, kVTVideoEncoderSpecification_RequiredLowLatency, kCFBooleanTrue);
722#endif
723
724 OSStatus status =
725 VTCompressionSessionCreate(nullptr, // use default allocator
726 _width,
727 _height,
728 kCMVideoCodecType_H264,
729 encoderSpecs, // use hardware accelerated encoder if available
730 sourceAttributes,
731 nullptr, // use default compressed data allocator
732 compressionOutputCallback,
733 nullptr,
734 &_vtCompressionSession);
735
736#if defined(WEBRTC_MAC) && !defined(WEBRTC_IOS) && ENABLE_VCP_ENCODER
737 CFBooleanRef hwaccl_enabled = nullptr;
738 if (status == noErr) {
739 status = VTSessionCopyProperty(_vtCompressionSession,
740 kVTCompressionPropertyKey_UsingHardwareAcceleratedVideoEncoder,
741 nullptr,
742 &hwaccl_enabled);
743 }
744 if (status == noErr && (CFBooleanGetValue(hwaccl_enabled))) {
745 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Compression session created with hw accl enabled";
746 } else {
747 [self destroyCompressionSession];
748
749 // Use VCP instead.
750 int usageValue = 1;
751 auto usage = CFNumberCreate(nullptr, kCFNumberIntType, &usageValue);
752 CFDictionarySetValue(encoderSpecs, kVTCompressionPropertyKey_Usage, usage);
753 CFRelease(usage);
754
755 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Compression session created with VCP";
756 status =
757 webrtc::VCPCompressionSessionCreate(nullptr, // use default allocator
758 _width,
759 _height,
760 'ftvc',
761 encoderSpecs,
762 sourceAttributes,
763 nullptr, // use default compressed data allocator
764 compressionOutputCallback,
765 nullptr,
766 &_vcpCompressionSession);
767 }
768#elif defined(WEBRTC_MAC) && !defined(WEBRTC_IOS) && !(ENABLE_VCP_FOR_H264_BASELINE) && defined(WEBRTC_ARCH_X86_FAMILY)
769 CFBooleanRef hwaccl_enabled = nullptr;
770 if (status == noErr) {
771 auto result = VTSessionCopyProperty(_vtCompressionSession, kVTCompressionPropertyKey_UsingHardwareAcceleratedVideoEncoder, nullptr, &hwaccl_enabled);
772 _isUsingSoftwareEncoder = result == noErr ? !CFBooleanGetValue(hwaccl_enabled) : true;
773#if HAVE_VTB_REQUIREDLOWLATENCY
774 if (_isUsingSoftwareEncoder && _isH264LowLatencyEncoderEnabled && _vtCompressionSession && !_useVCP) {
775 VTCompressionSessionInvalidate(_vtCompressionSession);
776 CFRelease(_vtCompressionSession);
777 _vtCompressionSession = nullptr;
778
779 CFDictionarySetValue(encoderSpecs, kVTVideoEncoderSpecification_RequiredLowLatency, kCFBooleanTrue);
780 CFDictionarySetValue(encoderSpecs, kVTVideoEncoderSpecification_EnableHardwareAcceleratedVideoEncoder, kCFBooleanFalse);
781 status = VTCompressionSessionCreate(nullptr, // use default allocator
782 _width,
783 _height,
784 kCMVideoCodecType_H264,
785 encoderSpecs, // use hardware accelerated encoder if available
786 sourceAttributes,
787 nullptr, // use default compressed data allocator
788 compressionOutputCallback,
789 nullptr,
790 &_vtCompressionSession);
791 }
792#endif
793 }
794#else
795 // Provided encoder should be good enough.
796#endif // defined(WEBRTC_MAC) && !defined(WEBRTC_IOS) && ENABLE_VCP_ENCODER
797 if (sourceAttributes) {
798 CFRelease(sourceAttributes);
799 sourceAttributes = nullptr;
800 }
801 if (encoderSpecs) {
802 CFRelease(encoderSpecs);
803 encoderSpecs = nullptr;
804 }
805 if (status != noErr) {
806 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to create compression session: " << status;
807 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
808 }
809 [self configureCompressionSession];
810
811#if !defined(WEBRTC_WEBKIT_BUILD)
812 // The pixel buffer pool is dependent on the compression session so if the session is reset, the
813 // pool should be reset as well.
814 if (_vtCompressionSession)
815 _pixelBufferPool = VTCompressionSessionGetPixelBufferPool(_vtCompressionSession);
816#if ENABLE_VCP_ENCODER
817 else
818 _pixelBufferPool = webrtc::VCPCompressionSessionGetPixelBufferPool(_vtCompressionSession);
819#endif
820#endif
821 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
822}

824- (void)configureCompressionSession {
825 RTC_DCHECK([self hasCompressionSession]);
826 SetVTSessionProperty(_vtCompressionSession, _vcpCompressionSession, kVTCompressionPropertyKey_RealTime, true);
827#if ENABLE_VCP_FOR_H264_BASELINE
828 if (_useBaseline && _useVCP)
829 SetVTSessionProperty(_vtCompressionSession, _vcpCompressionSession, kVTCompressionPropertyKey_ProfileLevel, kVTProfileLevel_H264_ConstrainedBaseline_AutoLevel);
830 else
831#endif
832 SetVTSessionProperty(_vtCompressionSession, _vcpCompressionSession, kVTCompressionPropertyKey_ProfileLevel, ExtractProfile(*_profile_level_id));
833 SetVTSessionProperty(_vtCompressionSession, _vcpCompressionSession, kVTCompressionPropertyKey_AllowFrameReordering, false);
834#if ENABLE_VCP_ENCODER
835 if (_useVCP) {
836 SetVTSessionProperty(_vtCompressionSession, _vcpCompressionSession, kVTCompressionPropertyKey_Usage, 1);
837 }
838#endif
839 [self setEncoderBitrateBps:_targetBitrateBps frameRate:_encoderFrameRate];
840 // TODO(tkchin): Look at entropy mode and colorspace matrices.
841 // TODO(tkchin): Investigate to see if there's any way to make this work.
842 // May need it to interop with Android. Currently this call just fails.
843 // On inspecting encoder output on iOS8, this value is set to 6.
844 // internal::SetVTSessionProperty(compression_session_,
845 // kVTCompressionPropertyKey_MaxFrameDelayCount,
846 // 1);
847
848 // Set a relatively large value for keyframe emission (7200 frames or 4 minutes).
849 SetVTSessionProperty(_vtCompressionSession, _vcpCompressionSession, kVTCompressionPropertyKey_MaxKeyFrameInterval, 7200);
850 SetVTSessionProperty(
851 _vtCompressionSession, _vcpCompressionSession, kVTCompressionPropertyKey_MaxKeyFrameIntervalDuration, 240);
852}

854- (void)destroyCompressionSession {
855 if (_vtCompressionSession) {
856 VTCompressionSessionInvalidate(_vtCompressionSession);
857 CFRelease(_vtCompressionSession);
858 _vtCompressionSession = nullptr;
859 }
860#if ENABLE_VCP_ENCODER
861 if (_vcpCompressionSession) {
862 webrtc::VCPCompressionSessionInvalidate(_vcpCompressionSession);
863 CFRelease(_vcpCompressionSession);
864 _vcpCompressionSession = nullptr;
865 }
866#endif
867 _pixelBufferPool = nullptr;
868}

880- (void)setEncoderBitrateBps:(uint32_t)bitrateBps frameRate:(uint32_t)frameRate {
881 if ([self hasCompressionSession]) {
882 auto actualTarget = _isBelowExpectedFrameRate ? bitrateBps / kBelowFrameRateBitRateDecrease : bitrateBps;
883 SetVTSessionProperty(_vtCompressionSession, _vcpCompressionSession, kVTCompressionPropertyKey_AverageBitRate, actualTarget);
884
885 // With zero |_maxAllowedFrameRate|, we fall back to automatic frame rate detection.
886 if (_maxAllowedFrameRate > 0) {
887 SetVTSessionProperty(
888 _vtCompressionSession, _vcpCompressionSession, kVTCompressionPropertyKey_ExpectedFrameRate, frameRate);
889 }
890
891 // TODO(tkchin): Add a helper method to set array value.
892 int64_t dataLimitBytesPerSecondValue =
893 static_cast<int64_t>(_isBelowExpectedFrameRate ? actualTarget / 8 : actualTarget * kLimitToAverageBitRateFactor / 8);
894 CFNumberRef bytesPerSecond =
895 CFNumberCreate(kCFAllocatorDefault, kCFNumberSInt64Type, &dataLimitBytesPerSecondValue);
896 int64_t oneSecondValue = 1;
897 CFNumberRef oneSecond =
898 CFNumberCreate(kCFAllocatorDefault, kCFNumberSInt64Type, &oneSecondValue);
899 const void *nums[2] = {bytesPerSecond, oneSecond};
900 CFArrayRef dataRateLimits = CFArrayCreate(nullptr, nums, 2, &kCFTypeArrayCallBacks);
901
902 SetVTSessionProperty(_vtCompressionSession, _vcpCompressionSession, kVTCompressionPropertyKey_DataRateLimits, dataRateLimits);
903
904 if (bytesPerSecond) {
905 CFRelease(bytesPerSecond);
906 }
907 if (oneSecond) {
908 CFRelease(oneSecond);
909 }
910 if (dataRateLimits) {
911 CFRelease(dataRateLimits);
912 }
913
914 _encoderBitrateBps = bitrateBps;
915 _encoderFrameRate = frameRate;
916 }
917}
918
919- (void)updateBitRateAccordingActualFrameRate {
920 _frameCount++;
921 auto currentTime = rtc::TimeMillis();
922 if (!_lastFrameRateEstimationTime) {
923 _lastFrameRateEstimationTime = currentTime;
924 return;
925 }
926
927 auto timeDifference = currentTime - _lastFrameRateEstimationTime;
928
929 // Let's not check too often.
930 if (timeDifference < 1000) {
931 return;
932 }
933
934 auto frameRate = _frameCount * 1000 / timeDifference;
935 _lastFrameRateEstimationTime = currentTime;
936 _frameCount = 0;
937
938 bool isBelow = frameRate * kBelowFrameRateThreshold < _encoderFrameRate;
939 if (isBelow == _isBelowExpectedFrameRate) {
940 return;
941 }
942
943 _isBelowExpectedFrameRate = isBelow;
944 [self setEncoderBitrateBps:_encoderBitrateBps frameRate:_encoderFrameRate];
945}

947- (void)frameWasEncoded:(OSStatus)status
948 flags:(VTEncodeInfoFlags)infoFlags
949 sampleBuffer:(CMSampleBufferRef)sampleBuffer
950 codecSpecificInfo:(id<RTCCodecSpecificInfo>)codecSpecificInfo
951 width:(int32_t)width
952 height:(int32_t)height
953 renderTimeMs:(int64_t)renderTimeMs
954 timestamp:(uint32_t)timestamp
955 rotation:(RTCVideoRotation)rotation
956 isKeyFrameRequired:(bool)isKeyFrameRequired {
957 if (status != noErr) {
958 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "H264 encode failed with code: " << status;
959 if (isKeyFrameRequired)
960 _isKeyFrameRequired = true;
961 return;
962 }
963 if (infoFlags & kVTEncodeInfo_FrameDropped) {
964 if (isKeyFrameRequired)
965 _isKeyFrameRequired = true;
966 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "H264 encode dropped frame.";
967 return;
968 }
969 _isKeyFrameRequired = false;
970
971 BOOL isKeyframe = NO;
972 CFArrayRef attachments = CMSampleBufferGetSampleAttachmentsArray(sampleBuffer, 0);
973 if (attachments != nullptr && CFArrayGetCount(attachments)) {
974 CFDictionaryRef attachment =
975 static_cast<CFDictionaryRef>(CFArrayGetValueAtIndex(attachments, 0));
976 isKeyframe = !CFDictionaryContainsKey(attachment, kCMSampleAttachmentKey_NotSync);
977 }
978
979 if (isKeyframe) {
980 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Generated keyframe";
981 }
982
983 __block std::unique_ptr<rtc::Buffer> buffer = std::make_unique<rtc::Buffer>();
984 if (!webrtc::H264CMSampleBufferToAnnexBBuffer(sampleBuffer, isKeyframe, buffer.get())) {
985 return;
986 }
987
988 RTCEncodedImage *frame = [[RTCEncodedImage alloc] init];
989 // This assumes ownership of `buffer` and is responsible for freeing it when done.
990 frame.buffer = [[NSData alloc] initWithBytesNoCopy:buffer->data()
991 length:buffer->size()
992 deallocator:^(void *bytes, NSUInteger size) {
993 buffer.reset();
994 }];
995 frame.encodedWidth = width;
996 frame.encodedHeight = height;
997 frame.completeFrame = YES;
998 frame.frameType = isKeyframe ? RTCFrameTypeVideoFrameKey : RTCFrameTypeVideoFrameDelta;
999 frame.captureTimeMs = renderTimeMs;
1000 frame.timeStamp = timestamp;
1001 frame.rotation = rotation;
1002 frame.contentType = (_mode == RTCVideoCodecModeScreensharing) ? RTCVideoContentTypeScreenshare :
1003 RTCVideoContentTypeUnspecified;
1004 frame.flags = webrtc::VideoSendTiming::kInvalid;
1005
1006 _h264BitstreamParser.ParseBitstream(*buffer);
1007 auto qp = _h264BitstreamParser.GetLastSliceQp();
1008 frame.qp = @(qp.value_or(0));
1009
1010 BOOL res = _callback(frame, codecSpecificInfo, nullptr);
1011 if (!res) {
1012 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Encode callback failed";
1013 if (isKeyFrameRequired)
1014 _isKeyFrameRequired = true;
1015 return;
1016 }
1017 _bitrateAdjuster->Update(frame.buffer.length);
1018}

1021 return [[RTCVideoEncoderQpThresholds alloc] initWithThresholdsLow:kLowH264QpThreshold
1022 high:kHighH264QpThreshold];
